  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1995-11-29", 
    "text": "Amends Federal civil service law to permit a retired Federal employee over age 65 to continue additional optional life insurance coverage when the beneficiary is permanently disabled. Requires such retiree to pay the entire premium for such insurance through withholdings from the retiree's annuity or compensation."
  }, 
